message.content:
cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper deals with configuring deep Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) for low power spike event based computation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses training both fully connected and convolutional neural network (CNN) architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper introduces a new general backpropagation mechanism for learning synaptic weights and axonal delays, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also compares its method against existing SNN based learning approaches and standard ANN to SNN conversion techniques, which could suggest it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with temporal credit assignment policy for backpropagating error to preceding layers, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
